<!-- TOOLTIP - ENDS -->

<!-- DETAILS SECTION - BEGINS -->
	<a name="moreDetails"></a>
	<h4 class="mul-hdr-dbl-rule additional-detail-hdr">Additional Details</h4>

	<div class="col-24">
		<div class="js-mul-tabs-example mul-tabs">
			{% include "page-tabs" %}
			<div id="tabs-1">
				<p>
					Designers should use the Tooltip when the amount of information displayed is short in length (10-15 words maximum) and not critical to the user. For longer content (more than 15 words or images) use the <a href="/objects/descriptive-hover">Descriptive Hover</a>.
				</p>
			</div>
			<div id="tabs-2">
				<strong>Text</strong>
				<ul>
					<li>The designer should use concise language in the Tooltip, no more than 15 words.</li>
					<li>The Tooltip must be plain text. </li>
				</ul>

				<strong>Height/Width</strong>
				<ul>
					<li>The Tooltip has a maximum width of 200 pixels but can be smaller based on content.</li>
					<li>The height of the Tooltip should be dynamic and based on the content included.</li>
				</ul>

				<strong>Color</strong>
				<ul>
					<li>The Tooltip container should have a light blue (#e7f0f9) color background.</li>
					<li>The Tooltip container should have a light gray (#cccccc) border color.</li>
					<li>The Tooltip text will be dark gray (#333333).</li>
				</ul>

				<strong>Placement</strong>
				<ul>
					<li>The Tooltip's placement relative to the link should be dynamic, based on how much space is available.</li>
					<li>By default, the Tooltip should display above the link. However, if there is limited space, it should be able to dynamically shift to the bottom.</li>
				</ul>

				<strong>Accessibility</strong>
				<ul>
					<li>The Tooltip container will open when the user mouses over the parent element and will disappear when the user moves the mouse away from the parent element.</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			<div id="tabs-3">
				<strong>Cross browser compatibility</strong>
				<p>IE9 doesn't crop background gradients on containers with rounded corners, so we square the corners of every container so it looks just like IE8.</p>

				<h4 class="mul-hdr-rule">Dependencies</h4>
				<table class="mul-table mul-table-borders" id="" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" title="" summary="">
					<thead>
						<tr>
							<th width="" scope="col">Library</th>
							<th width="" scope="col">Location or Download</th>
						</tr>
					</thead>
					<tbody>
						<tr>
							<td>jQuery {{ global.jquery_version }}</td>
							<td>assets/scripts/core/lib/jquery</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td>jQuery Tooltipster 2.1.4</td>
							<td>assets/scripts/core/lib/jquery/plugins</td>
						</tr>
					</tbody>
				</table>
			</div>
			<div id="tabs-4">
				<ul>
					<li>The tooltip would open on tap. If the user taps the already open tooltip, it will close.</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			<div id="tabs-5">
			<!-- GET CODE - BEGINS -->
				<section class="col-24">

					<h5 class="mul-hdr-rule">HTML</h5>
					<p>
						Below are different class-based options you can use to modify the position of the tooltip in relationship to the text or object that you are using with a toolitp.
					</p>

					<div class="col-24">

						<div class="col-12 first">
							<h5>For individual text-based elements</h5>					
							<p>Use one of the follow classes to change the position of an individual text-based element on the page.</p>
							<ol>
								<li><code>js-mul-tooltip-hover-top</code></li>
								<li><code>js-mul-tooltip-hover-right</code></li>
								<li><code>js-mul-tooltip-hover-bottom</code></li>
								<li><code>js-mul-tooltip-hover-left</code></li>
							</ol>
						</div>
						<div class="col-12">
							<h5>For non-text based objects like icons, images, or form elements</h5>						
							<p>Use one of the follow classes to change the position of the tooltip with a group of icons or other non-text based objects like images or form elements.</p>
							<ol>
								<li><code>js-mul-tooltip-hover-top-object</code></li>
								<li><code>js-mul-tooltip-hover-right-object</code></li>
								<li><code>js-mul-tooltip-hover-bottom-object</code></li>
								<li><code>js-mul-tooltip-hover-left-object</code></li>
							</ol>
						</div>

					</div>

					<h5>Basic Tooltip</h5>
					<pre class="prettyprint linenums"><xmp>{% include "/objects/tooltip-default" %}</xmp></pre>

					<h5>Basic Tooltip With Abbreviation Tag</h5>
					<pre class="prettyprint linenums"><xmp>{% include "/objects/tooltip-abbr" %}</xmp></pre>

					<h5>Tooltip Group</h5>
					<pre class="prettyprint linenums"><xmp>{% include "/objects/tooltip-group" %}</xmp></pre>

					<h5>Tooltip In A Form</h5>
					<pre class="prettyprint linenums"><xmp>{% include "/objects/tooltip-input" %}</xmp></pre>

				</section>
			<!-- GET CODE - ENDS -->
			</div>

		</div>
	</div>
<!-- DETAILS SECTION - ENDS -->

</section>
